â€“ Sioux Falls, South DakotaEvery airline has increased cleaning, using EPA-approved cleaning agents that are designed to kill viruses and bacteria.
Most airlines are also cleaning the cabins multiple times a day, followed by a more extensive cleaning when the planes are on the ground overnight.
They also use HEPA filters, which can completely change a plane's air supply up to 30 times per hour.
It's also wiping down airport check-in kiosks multiple times per day and encouraging customers to check in remotely via the Fly Delta app.
John Cox is a retired airline captain with US Airways and runs his own aviation safety consulting company, Safety Operating Systems.